<ns4454:section xmlns:ns4454="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.qualityAttributes.modifiability.typesOfChanges">

  <ns4455:title xmlns:ns4455="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Types of changes</ns4455:title>
  <ns4456:para xmlns:ns4456="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Virtually any aspect of a system may require change and one quality measure of an
    architecture is then to estimate the cost associated with such changes.
  </ns4456:para>
  
  <ns4457:section xmlns:ns4457="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4458:title xmlns:ns4458="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Requirements for new use cases</ns4458:title>
    <ns4459:para xmlns:ns4459="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      A system implemented in an architecture should be able to cost effectively support
      the addition of new functionality which realizes new use cases.
    </ns4459:para>
  </ns4457:section>
  
  <ns4460:section xmlns:ns4460="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4461:title xmlns:ns4461="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Requirement changes to existing use cases</ns4461:title>
    <ns4462:para xmlns:ns4462="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The requirements for use cases supported by an existing architecture may change. This
      may involve changes in the <ns4463:emphasis xmlns:ns4463="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">preconditions</ns4463:emphasis> and/or 
      <ns4464:emphasis xmlns:ns4464="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">postconditions</ns4464:emphasis> of a service. 
    </ns4462:para>
  </ns4460:section>

  <ns4465:section xmlns:ns4465="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4466:title xmlns:ns4466="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Workflow changes</ns4466:title>
    <ns4467:para xmlns:ns4467="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      This may require
      <ns4468:itemizedlist xmlns:ns4468="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4469:listitem xmlns:ns4469="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4470:para xmlns:ns4470="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">adding or removing workflow steps,</ns4470:para></ns4469:listitem>
        <ns4471:listitem xmlns:ns4471="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4472:para xmlns:ns4472="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">replacement of workflow steps, or</ns4472:para></ns4471:listitem>
        <ns4473:listitem xmlns:ns4473="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4474:para xmlns:ns4474="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">changes to workflow steps.</ns4474:para></ns4473:listitem>
      </ns4468:itemizedlist>
    </ns4467:para>
  </ns4465:section>
  
  <ns4475:section xmlns:ns4475="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4476:title xmlns:ns4476="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Change in service provider</ns4476:title>
    <ns4477:para xmlns:ns4477="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      A system often delegates certain responsibilities to external service providers. At
      times one wants to or has to change from one service provider to another.
    </ns4477:para>
  </ns4475:section>
  
  <ns4478:section xmlns:ns4478="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4479:title xmlns:ns4479="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Change in platform</ns4479:title>
    <ns4480:para xmlns:ns4480="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      This includes changes in
      <ns4481:itemizedlist xmlns:ns4481="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4482:listitem xmlns:ns4482="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4483:para xmlns:ns4483="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the underlying hardware platform,</ns4483:para></ns4482:listitem>
        <ns4484:listitem xmlns:ns4484="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4485:para xmlns:ns4485="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the operating system used,</ns4485:para></ns4484:listitem>
        <ns4486:listitem xmlns:ns4486="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4487:para xmlns:ns4487="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the middle ware technology used, or  
        </ns4487:para></ns4486:listitem>
        <ns4488:listitem xmlns:ns4488="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4489:para xmlns:ns4489="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the component container like the servlet or EJB container
          or even the Java run-time environment itself.
        </ns4489:para></ns4488:listitem>
      </ns4481:itemizedlist>
    </ns4480:para>
  </ns4478:section>
  
  <ns4490:section xmlns:ns4490="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4491:title xmlns:ns4491="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Usability changes</ns4491:title>
    <ns4492:para xmlns:ns4492="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Usability changes include changes in the user work flows, presentation layer changes
      (including language changes),
      and changes to the performance requirements.
    </ns4492:para>
  </ns4490:section>
  
  
  <ns4493:section xmlns:ns4493="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4494:title xmlns:ns4494="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Changes to system capacity</ns4494:title>
    <ns4495:para xmlns:ns4495="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      A system is usually built for specified average and peak loads. Over time a system may
      need to carry more load. Examples include the number of concurrent users, the number
      of transactions to be processed and the amount of data to be fed.
    </ns4495:para>
  </ns4493:section>
  
  
</ns4454:section>